    "body": "Hello team,\r\n\r\nI have an exception when receiving a plugin event from a remote plugin.\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nuncaughtException: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: JSON data of the plugin event is malformed : Interfaces can't be instantiated! Register an InstanceCreator or a TypeAdapter for this type. Interface name: org.eclipse.keyple.core.service.PluginEvent\r\n\tat org.eclipse.keyple.core.service.ObservableRemotePluginAdapter.onPluginEvent(ObservableRemotePluginAdapter.java:318)\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy understanding is that the issue, comes from this \r\nhttps://github.com/eclipse-keyple/keyple-service-java-lib/blob/78d54e7171f7db7cf218b848f1a32283511d788e/src/main/java/org/eclipse/keyple/core/service/ObservableRemotePluginAdapter.java#L309-L313\r\n\r\n`PluginEventAdapter.class` should be used instead of the interface.\r\n\r\nI'm using the release `2.3.1` but as you can see in the linked code, it seems to be the same with `3.x`\r\n\r\nRegards",
